main event: A military sighting of a fast-moving star-like object was reported over the Atlantic on 28 March 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed moving at a constant altitude of 15,000 to 20,000 feet., The sighting lasted for 45 seconds., The object's heading was noted as 060 degrees at 62 degrees elevation., The sighting was classified as a probable satellite., The report indicated a low probability of it being an aircraft.
location: Atlantic Ocean, Unknown Region, Unknown Country
witness description: military personnel from the USCGC McCullough
